channel.title: Endar V4
channel.description:
Hi, Everyone
Sorry for reposting my old client i haven't been online for 2 years. I'm back now but creating Endar V5 474 Client and Server. I'm now working on Endar V5 aswell which will be released sometime this year 2010. It will be 474 client I am also creating a 474 for it.
[size=10pt][u][b]VERSION FEATURES[/b][/u][/size]
-No background yet but will be in future [black background] -New looping support only for windows, that means after you choose an option it will loop back to the main title screen -Deleted website stealer from v3 -New gui update manager -New gui to launch client or exit it -GUI and updater each have a icon that is a pic of an E -Fixed alot of bugs including the java heap error -After update extracts the archive -Cool look -New way to start client -Has exit option too -Uses cache 369 -Deob 317 -Windows only color is green -Added so it deletes archive after update -No more flames! -Zooming press F12
SCREENSHOTS
The GUI to launch the client: [img]http://goat-spirit.com/Images/guifinal.PNG[/img]
Updater GUI: [img]http://goat-spirit.com/Images/updatefinal.PNG[/img]
Launch Screen: [img]http://goat-spirit.com/Images/winfinal.PNG[/img]
Client Itself: [img]http://goat-spirit.com/Images/winclient.PNG[/img]
DOWNLOAD LINKS Main Download: http://endar.co.uk/clients/endarclient4.zip Megaupload: http://www.megaupload.com/?d=BX37AH4G Rapidshare: http://rapidshare.de/files/26932539/Endar_V4.zip.html
################################################
[size=10pt][u][b]Endar V5 (COMING SOON 2010)[/b][/u][/size] Endar V5 will be 474 but this time i am also going to be releasing a server with the client. :)
Main Page: http://endar.co.uk/forum/index.php?topic=2.0

This one in Endar V4 does not contain C#. But Endar V5 which i am working on does tho

WHY! Java is multi-platform, .net isn’t…

You can still code a full server in C# and it will still work fine with the Java client.

What about running the server on Linux? You’re a tool.

You can still run C# in linux. But i don’t know how to in linux anyway I would release Java Version and C# Versions anyway.

You can run C# but not Visual C# that uses the .net library.

WHY BOTHER MAKING 2 RELEASES? Make one…[/quote]

Good point really as more people seem to use Java for coding servers rather than C#.
